// HELP tdd with nodejs

https://mochajs.org/#getting-started

https://semaphoreci.com/community/tutorials/getting-started-with-node-js-and-mocha



steps
	install mocha and chai, using 'assert' from node js, so no need to install assert
	update package json with test node:
		"test": "./node_modules/.bin/mocha --reporter spec",

to run
	navigate to test folder and run
		c:\node_projects\api_tdd_mocha_chai\test>    npm test


to test Api **
http://mherman.org/blog/2015/09/10/testing-node-js-with-mocha-and-chai/#.WPC7fWnyvIU
https://www.npmjs.com/package/supertest

https://codeforgeek.com/2015/07/unit-testing-nodejs-application-using-mocha/

install 
using "supertest" and "should" pkgs to test api responses..

to run api
	open a command line and run server.js    // for api

to test api
	> npm test  // in the respective folder



